author: Mike Chiari
title: WWE's 1st Chinese Superstar Tian Bing Confirmed to Compete at WrestleMania 33
text: WWE's 1st Chinese Superstar Tian Bing Confirmed to Compete at WrestleMania 33 Photo credit: WWE.com. Mike Chiari Featured Columnist March 30, 2017 WWE announced Thursday that Tian Bing—the company's first China-born Superstar—will compete in the Andre the Giant Memorial Battle Royal on Sunday at WrestleMania 33 in Orlando, Florida. The news was made official with the following post on WWE's Instagram account: A photo posted by WWE (@wwe) The 22-year-old Bing signed with WWE in June and has plied his trade at the WWE Performance Center in Orlando since then. Bing has just one televised match under his belt in WWE, as he teamed with Ho Ho Lun in a loss to DIY in the NXT Dusty Rhodes Tag Team Classic. When he steps into the ring Sunday as part of the WrestleMania kickoff show, he will become the first Chinese wrestler to compete on the Grandest Stage of Them All. Bing will face off with several notable WWE Superstars in the match, including Big Show, Braun Strowman, Sami Zayn and Dolph Ziggler. Listen to Ring Rust Radio for all of the hot wrestling topics.
